The paper presents a new framework for solving optimization problems with a diseconomy of scale, which is a topic that can be studied in various subfields of computer science. The use of linear programming relaxation and the analysis of the integrality gap suggest that the paper may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The use of the decoupling inequality and the analysis of random variables suggest that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), or cs.IT (Information Theory).
